headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 28 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists for his 12th triple-double of the season, and the Denver Nuggets built a big lead before holding off the Orlando Magic 110-99 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's 12th triple-double leads Nuggets past Magic 110-99

events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 37 points to spark the New York Knicks to a 131-113 rout of the Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored a season-high 36 points, Zion Williamson had 27 points and nine rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans defeated the Los Angeles Lakers 128-111 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, Williamson pace Pelicans in 128-111 win over Lakers

headlines.description: — The last time the Phoenix Suns won seven consecutive road games, Chris Paul had yet to become an NBA All-Star, Devin Booker and Mikal Bridges were 10, and Deandre Ayton had not even started playing basketball.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns stay hot, Heat struggle again as Phoenix rolls, 110-100

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris hit a go-ahead jumper with 3:44 to play, scored another basket on the next possession and finished with 25 points and 13 rebounds to help the Philadelphia 76ers hold off the Golden State Warriors 108-98 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tobias Harris comes up big late as Sixers hold off Warriors

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — James Harden had 25 points and 17 assists to lead the Brooklyn Nets to a 116-112 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden has 25 points, 17 assists, Nets beat Blazers 116-112
